    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="159"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d159">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_WW1">Woodrow Wilson</persName> Papers</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName corresp="#p_WW1" type="from"
                            >Wilson</persName> to the Secretary of the Treasury</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_MWG1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">McAdoo</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-25">25 November,
                            1918</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mac</hi>: Of course I realize the force of the
                    recommendation which Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MWG1">William McAdoo</persName>
                        urges,<note n="29" xml:id="d159fn29">See Secretary <persName
                            corresp="#p_MWG1">McAdoo</persName>’s letter of Nov. 23, 1918, <ref
                            target="#pg_169">p. 169</ref>.</note> but I could not think of
                    appointing Mr. <persName>Root</persName>, because I have had more opportunities
                    than he has had <pb facs="0242" n="172" xml:id="pg_172"/> of knowing just how
                    hopeless a reactionary he is. I think his appointment would discourage every
                    liberal element in the world.</p>
                <p>In haste,</p>
                <p>Affectionately yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>[<persName corresp="#p_WW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                        </persName>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
